<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>put someone through • put someone through it</xh5><p> <i>put someone through—</i>1. cause smb. to go through an operation, a course of study, etc.: I was able to <u>put all my students through</u>, except three whose English was the weakest. 2. put smb. in touch with a person by telephone: He lifted the receiver—listened and then said: “<u>Put her through</u>.”</p><p><i>put someone through it—</i>subject a person to a severe test or trying experience: Evidently she had been <u>put through it</u> in the interval, for she was crying bitterly.</p> </entry>
